column5: hey folks, just wonderin if any one of ya's has been to wakomata lake. i heard the record smallie from there is 7 1/4 lbs. caught in 1993 i believe. anyway i was lookin to take a trip in there, for some pike/walleye. thanks in advance for any info.  JP
I have only fished lake trout at wakomata.....Never seen or heard of walleye but there is pike and smallies.    TDunn
ya i never heard of walleye there either.....
Not a lot of walleye in 220' of water
apparently it has walleye!  i've only heard of people fishing smallies and lakers as well though.  http://www.wakomata.com/fishing.html
I can't see where it says there are walleye, it just states the season...am I missing something?

i believe it is lists the species in wakomata along with their seasons.  that's how i read the paragraph anyways. often cottagers aren't too eager to disclose their lake having walleye due to how highly prized they are.
